Olga, Eugene,

could the two students from Pisa (Giampaolo Mele and Aurora Armiento), the 
one student from Genova (Stefano Caviglia) and the one 
student from Udine (Fioralba Ajazi), avoid to pay the tax in order to 
obtain the Visa for Russia, exactly as the students from Tor Vergata ?
There is a way for them to avoid the payment of taxes even if the 
Agreement is only between Tor Vergata and Lomonosov universities ?

If yes, as I hope, will they obtain such advantage going to apply for Visa 
also in the russian consulates of Genova and Milano, or they have to apply for 
Visa in the russian consulate of Rome (as do the Tor Vergata students) ?

[Of course, by "tax" I do not mean the health and baggage insurance, which 
is mandatory, and can be prepared in the russian consulate (at least in 
the one of Rome) when applying for visa with the invitation received from 
Lomonosov]

Carmine

