Subject:   	Rome part of the school: about lodging and meals
From:   	"Carmine Di Fiore" <difiore@axp.mat.uniroma2.it>
Date:   	Tue, May 29, 2012 11:07 am
To:   	mele@mail.dm.unipi.it (more)
Cc:   	eugene.tyrtyshnikov@gmail.com (more)
Priority:   	Normal
Options:   	View Full Header |  View Printable Version  | Download this as a file

You 7, another student-PhD student from Ukraina, and the russian 
students-PhD students (18), will be lodged in CampusX of Tor Vergata (see 
Google for info about CampusX), during the Rome part of the Rome-Moscow 
school.

Because of the high number (26) of students-PhD students guests in Rome 
for the Rome-Moscow school, at this moment we have agreed with the 
employee of CampusX and the International Relations office of Tor Vergata 
that each of such 26 students-PhD students should pay "no more than 70 
euro" for his/her lodging in CampusX from September 16 to September 30.
The remaining amount required for having the 26 lodgings will be paid to 
CampusX by the International Relations office of Tor Vergata university.

Students have to provide by themselves to meals. If they choose
suitable places (f.i. the mess of the University or the bars in the 
faculties, or the new restaurant in CampusX) where to eat,
or if they cook by themselves (they will have a cooking corner in their 
double-separated rooms), then less than 150 euro are needed for 
eating in Rome for two weeks.


P.S.

If some further student-PhD student-person would like to participate to 
the school and can pay by himself/herself all the amount required in order
to be lodged for two weeks in CampusX (at least 190 euro), please 
such student-PhD student-person should contact
directly the employee of CampusX

1) AFiorini@siram.it (Alex Fiorini),
2) CCavallaro@siram.it (Cristina Cavallaro), 
3) MMuntoni@siram.it (Monica Muntoni)
cc: difiore@mat.uniroma2.it

asking for the most convenient price, as a further
participant of the Rome-Moscow school organized under the clearance of the 
International Relations office of Tor Vergata University.

