Prof. Ikramov, lecturer of the Rome-Moscow school 2012, asks to me what 
are the basic knowledges about the subject "Algebra" of italian students.
I replied, with the help of a prof of Tor Vergata (TV), that they are the 
ones listed at the end of this message, for what concerns every math TV 
student.

I guess they are the same for you, ok?

Who among you has already attended a more advanced course dealing
with the mini-couse "Introduction to commutative algebra (Hilbert 
theorems, Groebner bases)" which will be held in the Rome part of the 
school by prof. Ikramov ?

What is precisely the math you know about the subject
"Introduction to commutative algebra (Hilbert
theorems, Groebner bases)" ?


---------- Forwarded message ----------
Date: Mon, 18 Jun 2012 23:42:31 +0200 (CEST)
From: Fabio Gavarini <gavarini@axp.mat.uniroma2.it>
To: Carmine Di Fiore <difiore@axp.mat.uniroma2.it>
Subject: Re: aiuto

Ciao Carmine,

   eccoti qui di seguito gli argomenti di ALGEBRA che ogni studente di Tor 
Vergata ha certamente fatto

   Sets, operations among sets tra insiemi. Relations, maps.
   Natural numbers and Induction Principle.
   Cardinality. Basics of combinatorial calculus.
   Integral numbers. GCD of integral numbers, and Euclidean algorithm. Prime 
numbers, factorization in Z.
   Rational numbers.
   Congruences in Z. Chinese Remainder's Theorem. Euler function.
   Complex numbers.
   Polynomials with numerical coefficients; GCD and factorization for 
polynomials.

   Groups; group morphisms, kernel and image. Subgroups, normal subgroups. 
Cosets; quotient groups. Fundamental Theorem of Homomorphisms (for groups). 
Isomorphism Theorems (for groups).
   Lagrange Theorem; Cayley's Theorem, Cauchy's Theorem. Abelian groups. The 
centre of a group.
   Symmetric groups, dyhedral groups.
   Direct products, semi-direct products;
   Commutators; derived subgroups, solvable groups.
   Group actions; orbits, stabilizers, fixed points. Adjoint action; 
conjugation, conjugacy classes, centralizer(s), inner automorphisms; Burnside's 
Formula, the Classes Formula.
   p-groups, Sylow subgroups; Sylow's Theorems.
   Finite abelian groups: structure and classification.

   Rings; ring morphims, kernel and image. Subrings, ideals. Cosets; quotient 
rings. Fundamental Theorem of Homomorphisms (for rings). Isomorphism Theorems 
(for rings).
   Commutative (unital) rings; the group of units, zero divisors. Polynomial 
rings. Prime ideals, maximal ideals.
   Integral domains. Euclidean domains. Principal Ideal Domains. Unique 
Factorization Domains.
   Irreducible elements; prime elements. Gauss Lemma. Eisenstein cryterion.
   Fields, field extensions. Finite, algebraic, trascendental extensions. 
Algebraically closed fields. Splitting fields. Finite fields. Fundamental 
Theorem of Algebra.

Subject:   	Re: riconoscimento crediti scuola estiva
From:   	georgiev@dm.unipi.it
Date:   	Tue, June 19, 2012 11:44 pm
To:   	mele@mail.dm.unipi.it
Cc:   	spinelli@dm.unipi.it
Priority:   	Normal
Options:   	View Full Header |  View Printable Version  | Download this as a file

Salve,

normalmente i nostri studenti chiedono prima della attivita' se si puo
fare riconoscimento. Per attivita' tipo scuole estive serve

1) certificato della partecipazione (No ore e eventuale voto del esame
finale)
2) un nostro professre di riferimento (in questo caso lei puo chiedere il
prof. Bini per esmepio) che puo certificare l'utilita' della scuola e dare
una valutazione dei crediti per riconoscimento
3) per tutti casi simile cerco di verificare in anticipo come e' preparata
l'assicurazione per i nostri studenti che vanno fuori

Cosi' nel suo caso rimane a sistemare solo i punti 1) e 2) e di fare una
domanda per riconoscimento consegnadola alla sign.ra Carla Spinelli.
Saluti
Vladimir G.




