Subject:   	some information about eating in Lomonosov Moscow State University (LMSU)
From:   	"Carmine Di Fiore" <difiore@axp.mat.uniroma2.it>
Date:   	Wed, June 20, 2012 2:59 pm
To:   	mele@mail.dm.unipi.it (more)
Priority:   	Normal
Options:   	View Full Header |  View Printable Version  | Download this as a file

You can have 
breakfast, lunch and dinner in messes which are in the same main building 
of LMSU where you will be lodged,  in every day, also Saturday and 
Sunday. Eating in such messes is very cheap.

Note that for breakfast the messes open at 8:00 , the big mess is the
one where I usually have gone in the past to have breakfast.
You find there tea, hot water for tea, ready glasses with fresh water and 
different fruit tastes and fruit pieces or with other characteristic dense 
drinks. You find several types of very good cakes. You find eggs and 
cheese on pieces of bread. Moreover of course you find what russian 
students usually eat during their breakfasts. I remember that Alberto Santini
(from Catania), in the first edition of the school, almost always ate russian
food during his breakfasts. One should try to follow his example in order to
live the school.
You do not find milk and coffee in the big mess, so you do not find for 
example cappuccino. However there is a little bar at the entrance of the 
the big mess (and other bars in other parts of the main building of LMSU) 
where you find milk, coffee, cappuccino (in such little bars you also 
find cakes, eggs and russian food). The problem of such bars is that
you cannot sit down around a four-places-table as you can do instead in 
the messes.
The big mess closes at 20:00, so, in order to have dinner there, you have 
to arrive at least at about 19:45. The little mess, more near to the 
sector E where probably we will be lodged, closes at 20:30. Perhaps in the 
little mess there is less choice of foods, but it can have advantages, 
in fact going there is as go in the kitchen, eat and come back to continue
the activity one is doing.
Also near the little mess there is a bar such as the one near the big 
mess.
The two messes I'm speaking about are in two opposite sides of the 
central part of the main building. There is also a more professional mess 
in the centre of the central part of the main building, at the first 
floor, which is certainly open from Monday to Friday at the hours around
lunch. Also near such central mess there is a bar.
>From Saturday evening to Sunday early in the morning the central part of 
the LMSU building is closed, however one can go from one side (little mess)
to the other side (big mess) via a secret, well known (to the russian 
students) trajectory (it is not needed to go out of the LMSU building, 
note that the LMSU building is very wide). You find russian students (or, 
more precisely, LMSU students, because they come from many countries)
everywhere even on Sunday and in late hours, since they live there.

With no more than 150 rubles you can surely have a good lunch or dinner in 
the messes.

Moreover, opposite to the big mess there is
- a little supermarket, open untill 01:00 (in the night) every day, even on
Saturday and Sunday,
- a store with every kind of fresh meat, and
- a little restaurant (certainly much more expensive than messes) open 
until 23:00.
One can buy food in the little supermarket and/or in the store of meats, 
and prepare/cook it in the kitchen that the persons of each floor of the 
dormitory have in common.

Also, near the little mess there is a very little supermarket, open until 
late in the evening.

I observed all the above data in the Moscow parts of the schools of 2010 
(October 10-24) and 2011 (September 2-17).

Of course, one can buy food, for instance italian food, out of the 
LMSU building, out of the University, and then cook it in the kitchen in 
the floor of the dormitory.

My plan for Monday September 3 at 8 am is to have breakfast in the 
big mess.

