Subject:   	FiumicinoAirport-->TorVergata-CampusX(viaMetroAstationAnagnina)
From:   	"Carmine Di Fiore" <difiore@mat.uniroma2.it>
Date:   	Mon, July 9, 2012 5:11 pm
To:   	nastja.kruchinina@gmail.com (more)
Cc:   	eugene.tyrtyshnikov@gmail.com
Priority:   	Normal
Options:   	View Full Header |  View Printable Version  | Download this as a file

How to reach CampusX (Tor Vergata Univ)
from Fiumicino airport (via metro A station Anagnina):
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
[An updated map is enclosed (something has changed with respect to 2011)]


In Fiumicino Airport catch the no-stop-train for Rome Termini railway station
(name: Leonardo express; fare: 14 euro; frequency: one every half-hour; 
schedule: 6:38, 7:08,..., 23:38; duration of travel: 31 minutes)

In Rome Termini railway station catch metro A in the direction 
"Anagnina", and get out the metro at the last stop: Anagnina.

Then, when you are going out the metro station Anagnina, as soon as you see
on your left an old tram with garden around it, you have the 
following three possible choices 1),2),3):

1) 
You go on the left and catch any "cotral (blu) bus" which passes through
Tor Vergata University.
Ask to the driver "Passa per l'Universita' di Tor Vergata?" If yes, catch it.

Then,

If it goes to "entrata Torrenova dell'autostrada A1", 
get out of the bus at the last stop before such entrata (entrance).
You are very near to CampusX, you have CampusX in front of you.

Otherwise, get out of the bus at the Faculties of Engineering-Economy, and 
on foot reach the beginning of the path that goes behind a little church (it
is the University chapel), walk on such path and soon you will see, 
in front of you, but yet a bit far, the cube
buildings of CampusX. In order to reach them, you will have to pass from 
the path to the road.

Of course, it is better for you to try to catch cotral (blu) buses which go to 
"entrata Torrenova dell'autostrada A1".

Note: All such "cotral-(blu)-buses-passing-through-TorVergata-University", 
before arriving to the stops mentioned above, 
pass near the Faculty of Science building, in its south part where is the 
TV Math Department (place of the lectures of the school).


2)
You go on the right and catch bus 20, and get out of the bus at the stop near
the University mess and chapel, you will see the latter on the right 
(such stop is soon after the stop at the Engineering and Economy 
faculties). Then proceed along the path as indicated in 1).

Note: All buses 20 pass near the Faculty of Science building, in its north 
part where is the TV Biology Department (3 hundred meters in the south 
direction you find the TV Math Dept).

Comparison of the choices 1) and 2): 
The bus 20 course is quite longer than cotral (blu) bus course.
The frequency of bus 20 races is higher than the frequency of cotral (blu)
bus races.

3) Look for the navetta of CampusX.
Check the schedule in CampusX web-site.
(course of CampusX navetta: CampusX - MedicineFaculty -
EngineeringEconomyFaculties - HumanitarianFaculty(Lettere e Filosofia) -
ScienceFaculty - LawFaculty - Metro A station "Anagnina", and viceversa)

Further notes:

- There is a cheaper way to move yourself from Fiumicino airport to
CampusX. Not worst, if one notice that in Rome Termini station it 
is a bit long the walk from the platform where Leonardo Express arrives 
and the place where one can catch metro A (because of works for building 
metro C). 
It is enough that you catch the alternative regional train FR1 that goes,
doing some intermediate stops, from Fiumicino Airport to Rome (fare: 8 euro;
frequency: every 15 or 30 minutes depending on the time). Note that such train
does not stop in Rome Termini railway station. 
Before catching it, ask if it stops at "stazione Roma Tuscolana" railway 
station (for almost all times it stops there); if yes, catch it and get 
out of the train in that station, after a 40-50 minutes travel.
Near Roma Tuscolana railway station (via a 5-10 minutes
outside walk) there is the metro A stop "Ponte Lungo" (it is a metro A stop
between Termini and Anagnina).
Catch metro A there, in the direction "Anagnina".

- You can go from Fiumicino to Rome Termini railway station also by 
cotral buses (or by private companies buses, for example: http://
www.terravision.eu/italiano/rome_fiumicino.html?adw=1).
Note that "cotral" are public buses.
Fare: about 4 euro. The cotral buses are not frequent as the trains;
however, they travel even during the night.

- taxi fare from Fiumicino to Rome Termini: 40 euro.
It is possible to catch a taxi also from Anagnina to CampusX.

- From Rome Termini railway station to Fiumicino airport via Leonardo 
express: Schedule: 5:52, 6:22,...,22:52; departure platforms: 23 or 24
(may be sometimes 25).

-
Fares local travel tickets (on bus-metro):
BIT 1,50 euro: 100 minutes of travel (starting from the time you stamp it);
BIG 6 euro: one day of travel (till the midnight of the day you stamp it); 
BTI 16,50 euro: three days of travel (till the midnight of the third day,
counting from the day you stamp it); 
CIS 24 euro: seven days of travel (till the midnight of the seventh day,
counting from the day you stamp it).

