Waiting for the invitations which could be ready in the next week,
I begin to say to you what we'll have to do (such information are useful 
also for italian not of Rome students):

1) book an appointment (available days Monday-Friday) at the web-site:
http://roma.rusturn.com/index.sdf?lang=it
(If you check now the procedure, you note that in the period
September 28-August 5 it does not seem possible to book appointments)

2) in the day of the appointment,
arrive in Via Nomentana 116 - 00161 (06/44235625 4149)
[autobus 90(fast) or 36(slow) from Rome Termini railway station]
at least half an hour before the appointment
with:

- money ( about <=50 euro, for the travel/luggage/health 
insurance, mandatory in order to obtain visa to Russia;
there is a russian company in the consulate which prepares such 
insurances; almost surely we do not have to pay the consulate tax thanks 
to the purpose of the visit (study) [it could be useful, in order to avoid 
the payment of such tax, to bring with you also the enclosed Agreement 
between TV and LMSU]; bring with you also about 150 euro if you want to 
buy rubles in Via Giolitti 97, 06/4467251 near Termini, hoping you find 
them )
- two bus tickets (for going to the consulate and for coming back; for 
example, if you leave from Termini station you have to catch bus 90(fast) 
or 36(slow); near the consulate there is no place where you find bus 
tickets)
- the passport
- the original of the invitation letter (which we are waiting for)
- the enclosed agreement of cooperation (it may be necessary)
- one photo "formato tessera" 3x4 
- one pen with black ink, and some white papers,
- a further identity document (it may be necessary)
- the two forms you find at the web addresses:
http://www.rusconsroma.com/index.sdf?lang=it
(visti per studio, visti per studenti)
http://www.rusconsroma.com/article.sdf/it/vistiital/2288
[Note: such forms are also enclosed to this e-mail]:

in one form you will have to write, in particular:

purpose(aim) of the visit: study (studio)
type of visa: humanitarian (umanitario)
number of entrances: single entry (1)
date of entrance and date of exit: arrival and departure dates (gg/mm/aa) 
[Be precise when you write such dates!]
what "ente" you want to visit: Lomonosov Moscow State University
place,itinerary: Moscow (Mosca),

in the other form:

you could in particular ask to be authorized (when you will 
go back to the consulate to draw the passport with the russian visa 
stamped over it) to draw the passport with visa for a number of persons 
instead of for yourself only.

3) go back (4-10 days later) to the consulate to obtain
the passport with the russian visa stamped over it


