Alternative ways for going from Metro A station "Anagnina" to CampusX, 
whose precise address is Via di Passolombardo, 431 - 00133 Roma Tor 
Vergata (and, viceversa, from CampusX to Metro A Anagnina):

------------------

By taxi

Until 01:00am  you surely find taxi at the exit of Metro A 
Anagnina, near the starting points of buses 506-507-046 (see the map dwawn 
by hand I sent you). In the worst case, phone to the Rome taxi number
06 3570 ; at any time they answer.

--------------------

By bus 506-507-509

(the starting point of 509 is near the starting point
of 506-507-046)

Such buses go to CampusX (or to the neighbours of CampusX) from the south, 
so they do a longer course (than the buses 20, cotral blu, and CampusX 
navetta cited in my previous email) and do not pass through the university.

On Monday-Saturday:

If you catch 506 (with direction "Vanvitelli"): get out the bus at the 
stop "Passolombardo-Carpene" (last course: 00:00=midnight)

If you catch 507 (with direction "Grotte Celoni"): get out the bus at the 
stop"Tor Vergata-Palosci", and go along Via Berkeley (for 600 m) (last 
course 00:00=midnight)

If you catch 509 (with direction "Fosso del Cavaliere"): get out the bus 
at the stop "Tor Vergata-Palosci", and go along Via Berkeley (600 m) (last 
course: 19:30)

On Sunday:

You can catch only 507  (with direction "Grotte Celoni"): get out the bus 
at the stop "Passolombardo-Carpene" (last course: 00:00=midnight)

-------------------
Note:
Bus stop "Passolombardo-Carpene" is very near the entrance of CampusX.
Bus stop "Tor Vergata-Palosci" is 600m far from the entrance of CampusX
      SEE THE ENCLOSED MAP campusX.png

Advise:
For who arrives at Anagnina within midnight the advise is to look 
for 506 if Monday-Saturday or for 507 if Sunday, and catch it. You will 
arrive exactly at the entrance of CampusX (bus stop 
"Passolombardo-Carpene").
For who arrives at Anagnina after midnight, if 506-507 is absent, then 
catch a taxi

-------------------
Note: Last course (in the evening) of the Bus 20 I cited you in my
previous email: 00:00=midnight


*****************************
*****************************


OTHER WAYS FOR GOING FROM FIUMICINO AIRPORT TO ROME TERMINI (AND 
VICEVERSA)

At the main exit of Rome Termini railway station you find a square
with many buses under trees (piazza dei cinquecento). There, on the 
left, in the direction of the beginning of Via Cavour, in front of Museo 
Nazionale Romano (exactly on the border between a large street full of 
running cars and the zone with buses and trees), there is the bus stop in 
Roma Termini of the cotral bus linking Roma Tiburtina (Fiumicino airport) 
to Fiumicino airport (Rome Termini).
You recognize such bus stop from a placard
where it is written:

"
COTRAL
COLLEGAMENTO
Fiumicino <--(Roma Termini)--> Roma Tiburtina
... schedule ... cost of the ticket (the latter 
information are not updated there)
"

For more information and schedule, and for where to buy tickets for 
such bus in the airport, see the enclosed file 
Tiburtina_Termini_Fiumicino 
(http://www.cotralspa.it/PDF_Areoporti/tiburtina_termini_fiumicino.pdf) 
[In the enclosed file "19:00 festiva" means that the 19:00 race works 
only on festive days, for instance on Sundays].
In Rome Termini you find the ticket for example in a tobacconist that you 
meet (among all other shops) underground, going out of the metro. The 
cost of the ticket is 5 euro, if you buy it so. May be it is more (7-8 
euro) if you buy it on the bus.

The stop in the airport of such Cotral bus is outside T1 (Terminal 1), 
arrivals level.
See also See the enclosed FiumAirpMap 
(http://www.adr.it/pax-fco-mappa-dell-aeroporto).

Note: the arrivals level should be the lower level.

---------------------

At the bar-shops TERRAVISION in Fiumicino or in Rome Termini you
can buy ticket for going to Rome Termini or to Fiumicino by a Terravision
bus (6 euro).
You could also buy a ticket for both travels (11 euro).

Fiumicino Airport (bus stop in Via Baracca, near T(erminal)3 arrivals;
bus stops located in the parking area in front of T3, arrivals level)
[tickets in the T(erminal)3 terravision desk]
[See also See the enclosed FiumAirpMap
(http://www.adr.it/pax-fco-mappa-dell-aeroporto)].
               <-->
Rome Termini (stop on the right-exit of railwaystation, assuming you 
arrive by train)
[tickets in the near terravision bar-shop]

Schedule departures from Fiumicino airport: 5:35, ..., 23:00
Schedule departures from Rome Termini: 4:40, ..., 21:50
(frequency: one every 40-60 minutes: duration of the course: about 50 
minutes)

Note that the course of such Terravision buses is the following:
Fiumicino-->Fiumicino airport-->Rome Termini;
Rome Termini-->Fiumicino airport-->Fiumicino.

***********************
***********************

Further connections Metro A Anagnina <--> Math Dept of Fac Science

Besides bus 20, blu cotral bus, and CampusX navetta (see my previous 
email), also buses 500 and 046 connect Metro A Anagnina with the Dept of 
Math of the Faculty of Science (as you see also in the map drawn by hand I 
sent you)


**********
**********

See the enclosed FiumAirpMap where you find a place in the 
Fiumicino airport where you can rent a car


*****
*****


newsagents, tobacconists, machines (where to buy bus tickets, for instance 
the 7 days ticket in Rome)



